- "treasure's value" refers to the total contract value;
- "likelihood of claiming it" refers to the probability of closing the opportunity.

- 'Closed Won' indicates that the opportunity has been successfully converted into a deal;
- 'New Business' refers to opportunities that are from new customers or new projects;
- 'Probability = 1.0' means there is a 100% chance of the opportunity being closed successfully.

- 'closed won' refers to opportunities that have successfully been converted into sales;
- 'above-average value' refers to opportunities with a total contract value greater than the average total contract value of all opportunities;
